data.text:
James Blunt will return to Poland for an exclusive concert.

James Blunt, the British singer-songwriter known for his extraordinary talent in creating emotional songs, will come to the Polish capital to share his unique repertoire. He will present an array of the best songs that fill his musical output. Over the course of nearly 20 years, he has amassed a sizeable collection of hits for which he is recognised the world over. These range from the moving You're Beautiful and Goodbye My Lover to the dance-inducing Bonfire Heart and Heart to Heart. At the concert in Warsaw, the artist is sure to sing his latest hit, which has been topping the European charts for the past few weeks, Beside You from his latest album entitled Who We Used To Be. Who We Used To Be. A music video directed by Craig Bingham has also already been released, evoking memories of the singer's past.

Who We Used To Be is James' first studio album since Once Upon A Mind - acclaimed as one of the top three UK albums of 2019. This time around, James Blunt has collaborated with a variety of producers that include: Jonny Coffer, Red Triangle, Jack & Coke and Steve Robson. His recent collection of greatest hits collected on the album release The Stars Beneath My Feet went gold, selling over 100,000 copies.
